relevant_findings.general: Patient in no acute distress, comfortable, and appropriate
relevant_findings.HEENT: Normocephalic, atraumatic, pupils equal, round, responsive to light and accommodation, extraocular movements intact, sclerae anicteric, moist mucous membranes, oropharynx clear
relevant_findings.lungs: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no rales, rhonchi, or wheezing, good air movement, respiratory effort unlabored, no use of accessory muscles
relevant_findings.heart: Point of maximal impulse non-displaced, regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops, normal S1 and S2
relevant_findings.abdomen: Obese, non-tender bowel sounds present, soft, tenderness to palpation in the left lower quadrant and inferior to umbilicus, no masses or hepatosplenomegaly, no rebound tenderness or guarding
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, well-perfused, no cyanosis, clubbing, or edema, 2+ peripheral pulses (radials, dorsalis pedis), left second digit with ulceration at the tip without surrounding erythema or appreciable drainage
relevant_findings.neurological: Awake, alert and oriented to person, place, and time, cranial nerves II-XII grossly intact, muscle strength intact throughout, sensation intact generally with exception of lack of sensation below the knees bilaterally due to neuropathy
